Source: images2zip
Section: utils
Priority: optional
Maintainer: Package Maintainer <maintainer@example.com>
Build-Depends: debhelper-compat (= 13)
Standards-Version: 4.6.0
Homepage: https://github.com/shay1987/images2zip
Rules-Requires-Root: no

Package: images2zip
Architecture: all
Depends: ${misc:Depends}, docker.io | docker-ce, zip
Description: Download Docker images and bundle them into a zip archive
 images2zip reads a list of Docker image references from a text file,
 pulls each image, saves it as a tar archive, and creates a zip archive
 containing all generated tar files.
 .
 Useful for transferring Docker images to air-gapped environments or
 creating portable image bundles.
